{
  "texts": [
    "The Internet of Things (IoT) is redefining agriculture by transforming traditional farming into a dynamic, data-driven, and sustainable system tailored to meet the growing global food demand.",
    "As a technology that integrates interconnected sensors, devices, and data analytics, IoT has unlocked unprecedented opportunities for precision agriculture, resource optimization, and predictive decision-making.",
    "By 2050, agricultural production must increase by 70% to sustain an estimated global population of 10 billion (Grimblatt 2021; Molotoks et al. 2021).",
    "Achieving this growth within the constraints of finite resources and environmental concerns demands innovative solutions, with IoT emerging as a cornerstone of smart farming practices.",
    "IoT applications in agriculture span diverse areas, including automated irrigation, soil and crop monitoring, livestock health tracking, and disease prevention, empowering farmers to optimize resource usage and boost productivity (Cihan 2023; Srivastava et al. 2023)."
  ]
}